The paper proposes a novel approach for saliency detection using a recurrent attentional convolutional-deconvolution network. This involves using spatial transformer and recurrent network units to iteratively attend to selected image sub-regions for saliency refinement. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with image processing and analysis. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional-deconvolution networks and recurrent networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of context-aware features, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). 

Overall, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.IR.
